<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-11-0798 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this chapter the indications for the use of CT scanning, cerebral angiography,and plain skull films in the evaluation of the head injured patient arediscussed and the radiographic appearance of the more common traumaticlesions are illustrated. In addition the potential role of magnetic resonanceimaging (MRI) in the management of the head injured patient is delineated.</TEXT></DOC>